snippet.textDisplay:
Stop wandering to find the answer,
Take a pause,
Yeah, its true permanence is a lie,
Nature will float you without a query about why
I am weak and weary but my ego zips my tongue tight to tell the world,
I was misguided since the morning
And the night always carries bags full of guilt, regrets, overthinking doubts...
It feels like my feeling got fainted long back,
And now they gain their consciousness when the timing fails to support the situation,
After my mom's transition from a superwoman to an angelic woman,
My soul died
To fit in, to not bother anyone I always lied,
From those stupid attention-seeking habits to a person who is too mysterious to understand
I completely evolve into a different personality
Yeah I was coy
But not a person who hated people
Even my closed ones suffocate me,
I don't have answers,
I find peace with myself but I am too toxic for me,
I am my friend and enemy
I govern myself, I set to the task, accomplish them to increase the points of pride,
But now i quit
